The paper deals with the problem of data collection in a mobile sensor network with energy harvesting, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a scheduling optimization problem, which involves maximizing the amount of collected data while ensuring fair data reception, which is a problem that can be studied in the context of distributed systems (cs.DS) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the issue of energy harvesting, which is a topic that falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI, followed by cs.DS, cs.MA, cs.SY, and cs.IT.
